Section 1.1: QEMU's Event Loop Architecture

The Analogy That Sticks

QEMU's main loop = Node.js event loop

· Single-threaded (mostly)
· Non-blocking I/O
· Callbacks for events
· But QEMU adds threads for CPU and I/O

The GIL Parallel = BQL (Big QEMU Lock)

· Serializes access to shared state
· Prevents concurrent device emulation
· Major scalability bottleneck

Coroutines = Async/Await

· Stackful, not stackless
· Cooperatively scheduled
· Yield when waiting for I/O

The Three Thread Types

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    QEMU THREAD MODEL                            │
│                                                                 │
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │
│  │              MAIN THREAD                                │   │
│  │  • Holds BQL                                           │   │
│  │  • Runs event loop (glib GMainLoop)                    │   │
│  │  • Handles device emulation                            │   │
│  │  • Processes monitor commands                          │   │
│  │  • Manages migration                                   │   │
│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │
│                              ↓ (BQL)                            │
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │
│  │              vCPU THREADS                               │   │
│  │  • One per guest CPU                                   │   │
│  │  • KVM: kvm_cpu_exec() → KVM_RUN ioctl                │   │
│  │  • TCG: tcg_cpu_exec() → execute TBs                  │   │
│  │  • Acquire BQL only for MMIO/PIO                       │   │
│  │  • Run without BQL for most guest code                 │   │
│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │
│                              ↓ (No BQL)                         │
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │
│  │              I/O THREADS (IOThread)                     │   │
│  │  • Optional, created with -object iothread             │   │
│  │  • Each has its own AioContext                         │   │
│  │  • Handles block I/O (virtio-blk, etc.)                │   │
│  │  • No BQL held                                         │   │
│  │  • Can process I/O in parallel                         │   │
│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

