Section 2.1: IOThread Architecture

Why IOThreads Exist

Problem: All I/O in the main loop serializes through BQL.

Solution: Move I/O processing to dedicated threads.

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    WITHOUT IOTHREADS                           │
│                                                                 │
│  Main Thread (holds BQL)                                       │
│      ↓                                                         │
│  All block I/O (virtio-blk)                                   │
│      ↓                                                         │
│  BQL contended by vCPUs + main thread                         │
│      ↓                                                         │
│  Scalability bottleneck                                        │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    WITH IOTHREADS                              │
│                                                                 │
│  Main Thread (BQL)           │  IOThread 1 (no BQL)           │
│  • VNC, QMP                 │  • virtio-blk queue 0          │
│  • Monitor                  │  • Data plane                   │
│  • Migration                │                                │
├─────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────┤
│  vCPU Threads (BQL for MMIO) │  IOThread 2 (no BQL)          │
│                              │  • virtio-blk queue 1         │
│                              │                                │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

Creating an IOThread

```bash
# QEMU command line
-object iothread,id=iothread1
-object iothread,id=iothread2
-device virtio-blk-pci,drive=drive0,iothread=iothread1
-device virtio-blk-pci,drive=drive1,iothread=iothread2
```

IOThread Internal Implementation

```c
// iothread.c
typedef struct IOThread {
    Object parent;
    GMainContext *ctx;        // Glib context
    AioContext *aio_context;  // QEMU's AioContext
    QemuThread thread;        // The actual thread
    bool stopping;
} IOThread;

// IOThread entry point
static void *iothread_run(void *opaque) {
    IOThread *iothread = opaque;
    
    // 1. Create AioContext
    iothread->ctx = g_main_context_new();
    iothread->aio_context = aio_context_new(...);
    
    // 2. Run event loop (no BQL!)
    while (!iothread->stopping) {
        // Wait for events (block I/O completions)
        aio_poll(iothread->aio_context, true);
    }
    
    return NULL;
}
```

