Section 3.1: Profiling the Event Loop

Finding Bottlenecks with perf

```bash
# Profile QEMU main loop
perf record -g -p $(pgrep qemu) -- sleep 10
perf report -g graph

# Look for:
# - os_host_main_loop_wait() time
# - g_main_context_dispatch() time
# - vCPU thread blocking on BQL
# - I/O completion handling
```

What to Look For

High wait time in main loop:

· Not enough I/O? Use polling mode
· Too many file descriptors? Reduce VNC/QMP connections

High dispatch time:

· Too many callbacks? Batch them
· Expensive device emulation? Offload to IOThread

BQL contention:

· Move I/O to IOThreads
· Reduce MMIO frequency in guest

