Section 4.1: AioContext and the Block Layer

BlockDriverState and AioContext

```c
// block/block-backend.c

// Each BlockDriverState is associated with an AioContext
typedef struct BlockDriverState {
    AioContext *aio_context;   // Where I/O is processed
    // ...
} BlockDriverState;

// Get the context
AioContext *ctx = bdrv_get_aio_context(bs);

// Change context (for migration)
void bdrv_try_set_aio_context(BlockDriverState *bs, 
                               AioContext *ctx) {
    // Notify users that context is changing
    bdrv_aio_context_notify(bs, old_ctx, ctx);
    // Move the BDS to the new context
    bs->aio_context = ctx;
}
```

Drained Sections

```c
// Drained section = ensure no I/O is in flight
void monitor_command(BlockDriverState *bs) {
    AioContext *ctx = bdrv_get_aio_context(bs);
    
    // 1. Acquire context
    aio_context_acquire(ctx);
    
    // 2. Drain I/O (wait for pending requests)
    bdrv_drained_begin(bs);
    
    // 3. Do the operation (safe, no concurrent I/O)
    // ... modify block device ...
    
    // 4. End drained section
    bdrv_drained_end(bs);
    
    // 5. Release context
    aio_context_release(ctx);
}
```

